questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot service suffers from progressive performance degradation and eventual `OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space`. The service processes batch requests using a shared thread pool. Here is the suspicious code snippet:

java
@Service
public class OrderProcessingService {
    private static final ThreadLocal<List<Order>> orderCache = ThreadLocal.withInitial(ArrayList::new);

    @Transactional
    public void processBatch(List<OrderDto> dtos) {
        for (OrderDto dto : dtos) {
            Order order = convertAndValidate(dto);
            orderCache.get().add(order);
        }
        persistOrders(orderCache.get());
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application using Hibernate and PostgreSQL experiences a sudden surge in JVM heap memory usage and high CPU utilization. Thread dumps reveal hundreds of threads blocked waiting for database connections from the HikariCP pool. You find the following code in a key service:

java
@Transactional
public void processTransaction(Long id) {
    User user = userRepository.findById(id).orElseThrow();
    byte[] data = externalHttpClient.fetchLargePayload(user.getApiUrl());
    user.setPayload(data);
    userRepository.save(user);
}


Assume `externalHttpClient.fetchLargePayload` performs a blocking network call taking 5 to 10 seconds to respond.
